IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDesc: To improve access to health care for low income patients.
IRS990.MissionDesc: To provide access to quality, cost-effective health and oral (dental) care to the community, especially where there is a shortage, through the development and implementation of programs without regard to age, race, nationality, gender, sexual orientation, religion, political beliefs or ability to pay. We believe that all people have the right to quality health care and that such access will improve the health of the entire community.
IRS990.Desc: Provide non-emergency health care, preventative health maintenance and health education to medically underserved citizens in the local community.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Form 990, Part VI, Section B, line 12c
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: The Organization requires officers, directors, and key employees to disclose in writing all relationships that would potentially create a conflict of interest. The Organization requires the disclosures and updates to be made at least annually.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Form 990, Part VI, Section B, line 15
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: Compensation for the CEO is determined by the Board of Directors annually and is based on a performance evaluation and the overall market conditions. Compensation for key employees is determined by annual reviews, which are completed by the CEO.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Form 990, Part VI, Section C, line 19
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: The Organization makes its governing documents, conflict of interest policy, and financial statements available to the public upon request.
